name: FAREWELL to Flair Airlines' 737-400! Toronto to Calgary (via Winnipeg)
description:
Along with many other aircraft retirements around the world this year, Flair has officially said goodbye to their Boeing 737-400s.

While these were planned to leave the fleet by the end of the year, their final revenue flights took place in March, and the remaining three aircraft had been stored. 

Throughout August, they all departed Canada for a new owner, quietly closing this chapter in Flair Airlines' history.

So long, 737-400!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

DISCLAIMER: The ticket for this flight was paid for by Flair Airlines. This video was not pre-approved by Flair Airlines and all opinions are my own.
